cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DC

The paper presents a meta-model for multi-level agent-based models, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (MAS). Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the influence/reaction principle, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (AI) and social simulation (SI), making cs.AI and cs.SI likely sub-categories as well. The meta-model also has potential applications in systems and control (SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC), which are also possible sub-categories.
